<bug>
    <id>341132</id>
    <title>Firefox should use system settings from KDE for fonts</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Currently I'm running Firefox nightly from trunk: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; U; Linux i686; en-US; rv:1.9a1) Gecko/20060610 Minefield/3.0a1.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">When you install Firefox it uses its own default settings for fonts (interface and web pages).</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Firefox should be more integrated with KDE desktop and use font settings from KDE Control Center as default settings for fonts.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">If user doesn't explicitly change the settings from Firefox Preferences then Firefox should also follow the changes to font settings in KDE Control Center.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
